Hasenpfeffer-Rabbit-Stew

A savory stew made by marinating and braising rabbit in spices and vinegar. 

Ingredients:
One large rabbit, dressed, and cut into pieces
½ cup flour
½ teaspoon garlic powder
½ teaspoon onion powder
¼ cup olive oil
1 teaspoon salt
½  teaspoon pepper
½ teaspoon allspice or cloves
1 medium-sized onion
5 cloves garlic, peeled and sliced
2 bay leaves
½ cup vinegar
1 can tomato puree

Directions:
Combine garlic powder, onion powder, and flour.
Roll pieces of meat in flour mixture, and fry in the oil until golden brown.
Place the fried meat in a Dutch oven with the sliced onion, garlic, allspice, bay leaves, salt, pepper, vinegar, and tomato puree.
Bake at 350 for 1 to 1.5 hours.
